const faqs = [
  {
    question: "When does the missed call text go out?",
    answer: "The branded text reaches the caller's phone within seconds of the unanswered call — before they have scrolled to the next fabricator on Google. During busy workshop phases when you are welding gate frames, grinding staircase stringers, or assembling balustrade sections, this instant response keeps you on every potential client's shortlist."
  },
  {
    question: "What does the text message say?",
    answer: "You compose the text during setup and update it at any time. A typical fabrication workshop message reads: 'Thank you for calling [workshop name]. I am currently in the workshop and will return your call shortly. Reply with details of your metalwork project for a faster response.' The wording reflects your workshop's personality and professionalism."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this replace AI Phone Answering?",
    answer: "They operate as complementary layers. Phone Answering conducts full design conversations — gathering metalwork type, material, dimensions, finish preference, and timeline. Missed Call Text Back catches the edge cases — a caller who hangs up before the AI connects, or a mobile signal dropping inside the steel-framed workshop. Both together mean every metalwork enquiry is retained."
